# React Counter App

## Description

This project demonstrates the use of React State in a class component. It tracks the number of people entering and exiting a mall using Login and Exit buttons.

## Technologies Used

- React
- JavaScript (ES6)
- HTML
- CSS
- Node.js
- npm

## Features

- React State
- Class Component
- Event Handling
- Button Click Counter
- Dynamic UI Updates

## Project Structure

```
counterapp
│
├── src
│   ├── Components
│   │   └── CountPeople.js
│   ├── App.js
│   └── index.js
```

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/counterapp.git
cd counterapp
npm install
npm start
```

## Output

- **Login** button increments the **People Entered** count.
- **Exit** button increments the **People Left** count.
- The UI updates automatically using React State.

